Package: regexhelpeR
Title: Deals with regular expressions in dictionaries
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Johann",
           family = "Gr√ºndl",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "mail@johanngruendl.at",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6497-8188"))
Description: regexhelpeR is a small package to deal with regular expressions,
    mainly in dictionaries. It provides functions to switch between lazy and
    greedy patterns and to optimize performance for patterns. The functions are
    used in the packages multidictR and popdictR.
